        <updateDate>2024-07-01T22:23:58Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reauthorizing the Creating Opportunities that Necessitate New and Enhanced Connections That Improve Opioid Navigation Strategies Act of 2023 or the RECONNECTIONS Act of 2023&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill reauthorizes through FY2028 several programs that are administered by the Centers for Disease and Control Prevention to address opioid misuse.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Specifically, the bill reauthorizes evidence-based prevention grants, the prescription drug monitoring program, and education and awareness campaigns. It also specifically incorporates the fentanyl crisis as a new and emerging public health crisis that may be addressed through evidence-based prevention grants.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
